cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.NA, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper presents a new algorithm for performing Delaunay triangulation of sets of 2D points. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of a radially propagating sweep-hull as a novel component of the algorithm. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as Delaunay triangulation is a topic in discrete mathematics. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible category as the paper discusses the efficiency of the algorithm in empirical tests. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is a less likely category, but still possible as Delaunay triangulation is often used in computer graphics.
